# Spring Profile and Migration Templates

## Profile Strategy
- Keep base defaults in `application.yml`.
- Keep PostgreSQL config in `application-postgres.yml`.
- Keep MySQL config in `application-mysql.yml`.
- Activate profile by environment (`SPRING_PROFILES_ACTIVE=postgres|mysql`).

## Required Config Files
- `src/main/resources/application.yml`
- `src/main/resources/application-postgres.yml`
- `src/main/resources/application-mysql.yml`

## Base Application Template
- `application.yml` should include only shared defaults:
  - `spring.application.name`
  - `spring.jpa.open-in-view: false`
  - `spring.jpa.hibernate.ddl-auto: validate`
  - logging level defaults
  - management/actuator defaults
  - `spring.flyway.enabled: true`
- Do not hardcode vendor-specific datasource values in base file.

## PostgreSQL Profile Template
- `application-postgres.yml` should define:
  - `spring.datasource.url: jdbc:postgresql://...`
  - `spring.datasource.username`
  - `spring.datasource.password`
  - `spring.datasource.driver-class-name: org.postgresql.Driver`
  - `spring.jpa.database-platform: org.hibernate.dialect.PostgreSQLDialect`
  - `spring.flyway.locations: classpath:db/migration-postgres`

## MySQL Profile Template
- `application-mysql.yml` should define:
  - `spring.datasource.url: jdbc:mysql://...`
  - `spring.datasource.username`
  - `spring.datasource.password`
  - `spring.datasource.driver-class-name: com.mysql.cj.jdbc.Driver`
  - `spring.jpa.database-platform: org.hibernate.dialect.MySQLDialect`
  - `spring.flyway.locations: classpath:db/migration`

## Flyway Folder Structure
- Keep migrations under:
  - `src/main/resources/db/migration-postgres` (default)
  - `src/main/resources/db/migration` (MySQL compatibility)
- PostgreSQL uses `TIMESTAMP(6)` and separate `CREATE INDEX` statements.
- MySQL uses `DATETIME(6)` and inline `INDEX` declarations in `CREATE TABLE`.

## Migration Naming Convention
- Use versioned names:
  - `V1__init_schema.sql`
  - `V2__create_customer_table.sql`
  - `V3__add_customer_indexes.sql`
- Keep version numbers synchronized between databases.
- If one vendor needs an extra migration, document the reason in comments.

## Generation Checklist
- When generating config files, include both profile files.
- Keep secrets as environment variables, not literals.
- Ensure `postgres` profile works locally by default.
- Ensure `mysql` profile remains available for compatibility.
